        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 7:50AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 750 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southeast of Goodland, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Ord...                            Grant...
Corinne...                        Fallon...
Sobol...                          Swink...
Goodland...                       Sawyer...
Messer...                         Hugo Lake State Park...
Apple...                          Raymond Gary State Park...
Hugo...                           Huskey...
Fort Towson...                    Gay...
Arthur City...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
